# Golden Rules

These rules are the highest priority and must never be violated.

## Rules

- **No useEffect for data fetching.** Use dedicated async hooks/services for server data and keep fetching logic outside component effects.
- **No React Context for global state management.** Use Zustand stores for all client-side global state. Context causes unnecessary re-renders across the tree and does not scale.
- **No `any` type.** Every variable, parameter, return type, and generic must be properly typed. Use `unknown` if the type is truly not known, then narrow it. If a third-party library lacks types, create a declaration file.
- **No hardcoded colors.** Never use hex values (`#fff`), RGB (`rgb()`), HSL (`hsl()`), or raw Tailwind color classes (`text-red-500`). Always use semantic design tokens (`text-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `border-destructive`).
- **Always use the design system.** Use shadcn/ui components instead of raw HTML elements when an equivalent exists. Never build custom buttons, inputs, dialogs, etc. from scratch.
- **All user-facing strings must go through i18n.** Use the `useTranslation()` hook and translation keys for every string visible to users. No hardcoded English text in JSX.
- **No console.log in committed code.** Remove all `console.log`, `console.warn`, `console.error`, and `console.debug` statements before committing. Use the Sentry module for error reporting and structured logging.
- **No default exports.** Always use named exports for better refactoring support and explicit imports.

## Examples

### Good

```typescript
// Data fetching via dedicated hook/service
const { data: users, isLoading } = useUsersData();

// State management with Zustand
const count = useCounterStore((state) => state.count);

// Proper typing
function processItems(items: ReadonlyArray<Item>): ProcessedItem[] {
  return items.map(transformItem);
}

// Semantic color tokens
<div className="bg-background text-foreground border-border" />

// Design system components
<Button variant="destructive" size="sm">Delete</Button>

// i18n strings
const { t } = useTranslation();
<p>{t('dashboard.welcome_message')}</p>

// Error reporting via Sentry
import { captureAppError } from '@/modules/sentry';
captureAppError(new AppError('FETCH_FAILED', 'Could not load users'));
```

### Bad

```typescript
// useEffect for data fetching
useEffect(() => {
  fetch('/api/users').then(res => res.json()).then(setUsers);
}, []);

// Context for state management
const ThemeContext = createContext<Theme>('light');

// Using any
function processData(data: any) { return data.items; }

// Hardcoded colors
<div className="bg-[#1a1a2e] text-red-500" style={{ color: '#fff' }} />

// Raw HTML instead of design system
<button className="px-4 py-2 rounded bg-blue-500">Click</button>

// Hardcoded English text
<p>Welcome to the dashboard</p>

// console.log left in code
console.log('user data:', userData);

// Default export
export default function MyComponent() {}
```
